TITLE: Implementing Data Driven Tests in CodeceptJS
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to create and execute data-driven tests using DataTable in CodeceptJS. Demonstrates creating test scenarios that run with different data sets.
SOURCE: https://github.com/codeceptjs/codeceptjs/blob/3.x/docs/advanced.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
let accounts = new DataTable(['login', 'password']);
accounts.add(['davert', '123456']);
accounts.add(['admin', '123456']);

accounts.xadd(['admin', '23456'])

Data(accounts).Scenario('Test Login', ({ I, current }) => {
  I.fillField('Username', current.login);
  I.fillField('Password', current.password);
  I.click('Sign In');
  I.see('Welcome '+ current.login);
});
```

