TITLE: Implementing Conditional Retries in CodeceptJS Custom Helper
DESCRIPTION: Example of implementing conditional retries in a CodeceptJS custom helper to handle specific errors. This demonstrates how to use the global promise recorder to retry steps on certain conditions.
SOURCE: https://github.com/codeceptjs/codeceptjs/blob/3.x/docs/custom-helpers.md#2025-04-21_snippet_9

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
_before() {
  const recorder = require('codeceptjs').recorder;
  recorder.retry({
    retries: 2,
    when: err => err.message.indexOf('Cannot find context with specified id') > -1,
  });
}
```

