TITLE: Implementing Page Object Pattern in CodeceptJS
DESCRIPTION: Example of a page object implementation with field selectors and helper methods for form interactions. Shows how to structure page objects for maintainable test code.
SOURCE: https://github.com/codeceptjs/codeceptjs/blob/3.x/README.md#2025-04-21_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const { I } = inject()

module.exports = {
  fields: {
    email: '#user_basic_email',
    password: '#user_basic_password',
  },
  submitButton: { css: '#new_user_basic input[type=submit]' },

  sendForm(email, password) {
    I.fillField(this.fields.email, email)
    I.fillField(this.fields.password, password)
    I.click(this.submitButton)
  },
}
```

