TITLE: Implementing Custom Locators in CodeceptJS
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to implement custom locator strategies in CodeceptJS using the internal API. This example demonstrates creating custom strict locators and custom string locators.
SOURCE: https://github.com/codeceptjs/codeceptjs/blob/3.x/docs/locators.md#2025-04-21_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
codeceptjs.locator.addFilter((providedLocator, locatorObj) => {
  if (providedLocator.data) {
    locatorObj.type = 'css';
    locatorObj.value = `[data-element=${providedLocator.data}]`
  }
});

I.click({ data: 'user-login' });

codecepts.locator.addFilter((providedLocator, locatorObj) => {
    if (typeof providedLocator === 'string') {
      if (providedLocator[0] === '=') {
        locatorObj.value = `.//*[text()="${providedLocator.substring(1)}"]`;
        locatorObj.type = 'xpath';
      }
    }
});

I.click('=Login');
```

