TITLE: Basic API Testing with CodeceptJS
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates basic API testing features including sending GET requests and performing assertions on the response.
SOURCE: https://github.com/codeceptjs/codeceptjs/blob/3.x/docs/api.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
I.sendGetRequest('/users/1');
// returns { "user": { "name": "jon" }, "projects": [] }
I.seeResponseCodeIsSuccessful();
I.seeResponseContainsKeys(['user', 'projects']);
I.seeResponseContainsJson({ user: { name: 'jon' } });
I.seeResponseMatchesJsonSchema($ => {
  return $.object(
    user: $.object({
      name: $.string(),
    }),
    projects: $.array()
  )
});
```

