TITLE: Using Async Helper Functions in CodeceptJS
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates the correct usage of async functions in CodeceptJS, emphasizing the importance of using 'await' when calling functions that include grab actions.
SOURCE: https://github.com/codeceptjs/codeceptjs/blob/3.x/docs/basics.md#2025-04-21_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// a helper function
async function getAllUsers(I) {
  const users = await I.grabTextFrom('.users')
  return users.filter(u => u.includes('active'))
}

// a test
Scenario('try helper functions', async ({ I }) => {
  // we call function with await because it includes `grab`
  const users = await getAllUsers(I)
})
```

