TITLE: Configuring GraphQLDataFactory Helper
DESCRIPTION: Configuration example for GraphQLDataFactory helper showing endpoint setup, cleanup settings, headers, and factory definitions with mutation queries.
SOURCE: https://github.com/codeceptjs/codeceptjs/blob/3.x/docs/data.md#2025-04-21_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
GraphQLDataFactory: {
  endpoint: "http://user.com/graphql",
  cleanup: true,
  headers: {
    'Content-Type': 'application/json',
    'Accept': 'application/json',
  },
  factories: {
    createUser: {
      query: 'mutation createUser($input: UserInput!) { createUser(input: $input) { id name }}',
      factory: './factories/users',
      revert: (data) => ({
        query: 'mutation deleteUser($id: ID!) { deleteUser(id: $id) }',
        variables: { id : data.id},
      }),
    },
  }
```

